15/08/2006
ATHENS, Greece -- US Secretary of State Condoleezza Rice has sent a letter to Foreign Minister Dora Bakoyannis, expressing gratitude for Greece's assistance in evacuating Americans from Lebanon during the fighting between Israel and Hezbollah. According to Athens media reports Monday (14 August), Rice praised the efforts of the Greek missions in Nicosia, Beirut and Washington, as well as the crews of the Greek ships that transferred US evacuees from Lebanon. (ANA-MPA, Antenna - 14/08/06)
